<section id="performance">
  <h2>Performance</h2>
  <p>These attributes give the browser hints about loading priority, letting you speed up what matters and defer what doesn't.</p>

  <h3><code>loading</code></h3>
  <p>Controls when a resource starts loading. Use <code>loading="lazy"</code> on images and iframes below the fold to defer loading until the user scrolls near them.</p>
  <dl>
    <dt><code>lazy</code></dt>
    <dd>Defer loading until the element is near the viewport.</dd>
    <dt><code>eager</code></dt>
    <dd>Load immediately (the default).</dd>
  </dl>
  <p><strong>Applies to:</strong> <a href="/docs/elements/native/img/"><code>&lt;img&gt;</code></a>, <a href="/docs/elements/native/iframe/"><code>&lt;iframe&gt;</code></a></p>

  <h3><code>fetchpriority</code></h3>
  <p>Tells the browser how important a resource is relative to others of the same type. Use <code>fetchpriority="high"</code> on your LCP (Largest Contentful Paint) image.</p>
  <dl>
    <dt><code>high</code></dt>
    <dd>Fetch at a higher priority than normal.</dd>
    <dt><code>low</code></dt>
    <dd>Fetch at a lower priority than normal.</dd>
    <dt><code>auto</code></dt>
    <dd>Let the browser decide (the default).</dd>
  </dl>
  <p><strong>Applies to:</strong> <a href="/docs/elements/native/img/"><code>&lt;img&gt;</code></a>, <a href="/docs/elements/native/link/"><code>&lt;link&gt;</code></a>, <a href="/docs/elements/native/script/"><code>&lt;script&gt;</code></a></p>

  <h3><code>decoding</code></h3>
  <p>Hints whether image decoding should block rendering. Use <code>decoding="async"</code> on non-critical images to keep the main thread responsive.</p>
  <dl>
    <dt><code>async</code></dt>
    <dd>Decode off the main thread.</dd>
    <dt><code>sync</code></dt>
    <dd>Decode synchronously (blocks rendering).</dd>
    <dt><code>auto</code></dt>
    <dd>Let the browser decide (the default).</dd>
  </dl>
  <p><strong>Applies to:</strong> <a href="/docs/elements/native/img/"><code>&lt;img&gt;</code></a></p>

  <code-block language="html" label="Loading and priority">{{ loadingExample | escape }}</code-block>
  <code-block language="html" label="Image decoding">{{ decodingExample | escape }}</code-block>
</section>

<section id="mobile">
  <h2>Mobile UX</h2>
  <p>These attributes control the virtual keyboard and autofill behavior on mobile devices — small changes that dramatically improve the input experience.</p>

  <h3><code>inputmode</code></h3>
  <p>Controls which virtual keyboard appears on mobile. Critical for fields where <code>type</code> doesn't match the keyboard you want — like a PIN field that needs a numeric keyboard but isn't <code>type="number"</code>.</p>
  <dl>
    <dt><code>numeric</code></dt>
    <dd>Number pad (0-9). Use for PINs, zip codes, quantities.</dd>
    <dt><code>decimal</code></dt>
    <dd>Number pad with decimal point. Use for prices, measurements.</dd>
    <dt><code>tel</code></dt>
    <dd>Phone dialer layout.</dd>
    <dt><code>email</code></dt>
    <dd>Keyboard with <code>@</code> and <code>.com</code>.</dd>
    <dt><code>url</code></dt>
    <dd>Keyboard with <code>/</code> and <code>.com</code>.</dd>
    <dt><code>search</code></dt>
    <dd>Keyboard with a search/go action key.</dd>
    <dt><code>none</code></dt>
    <dd>No virtual keyboard (use for custom input UIs).</dd>
  </dl>
  <p><strong>Applies to:</strong> <a href="/docs/elements/native/input/"><code>&lt;input&gt;</code></a>, <a href="/docs/elements/native/textarea/"><code>&lt;textarea&gt;</code></a>, and any element with <code>contenteditable</code></p>

  <code-block language="html" label="Input mode examples">{{ inputmodeExample | escape }}</code-block>

  <h3><code>enterkeyhint</code></h3>
  <p>Controls the label on the Enter key of the virtual keyboard. Gives users a visual cue about what pressing Enter will do.</p>
  <dl>
    <dt><code>enter</code></dt>
    <dd>Generic Enter key.</dd>
    <dt><code>done</code></dt>
    <dd>Signals input is complete (closes keyboard on some devices).</dd>
    <dt><code>go</code></dt>
    <dd>Navigate to the entered value.</dd>
    <dt><code>next</code></dt>
    <dd>Move to the next field.</dd>
    <dt><code>search</code></dt>
    <dd>Execute a search.</dd>
    <dt><code>send</code></dt>
    <dd>Send a message.</dd>
  </dl>

  <code-block language="html" label="Enter key hints">{{ enterkeyhintExample | escape }}</code-block>

  <h3><code>autocomplete</code></h3>
  <p>Tells the browser what kind of data a field expects, enabling one-tap autofill on mobile. This is the single most impactful attribute for form conversion on mobile devices.</p>
  <p>Common values:</p>
  <dl>
    <dt><code>name</code>, <code>given-name</code>, <code>family-name</code></dt>
    <dd>Personal name fields.</dd>
    <dt><code>email</code>, <code>tel</code></dt>
    <dd>Contact information.</dd>
    <dt><code>street-address</code>, <code>postal-code</code>, <code>country</code></dt>
    <dd>Shipping/billing address.</dd>
    <dt><code>cc-number</code>, <code>cc-exp</code>, <code>cc-csc</code></dt>
    <dd>Payment card fields.</dd>
    <dt><code>username</code>, <code>current-password</code>, <code>new-password</code></dt>
    <dd>Authentication fields.</dd>
    <dt><code>one-time-code</code></dt>
    <dd>SMS/email verification codes (triggers autofill from notification).</dd>
    <dt><code>off</code></dt>
    <dd>Disable autofill for this field.</dd>
  </dl>
  <p><strong>Applies to:</strong> <a href="/docs/elements/native/input/"><code>&lt;input&gt;</code></a>, <a href="/docs/elements/native/select/"><code>&lt;select&gt;</code></a>, <a href="/docs/elements/native/textarea/"><code>&lt;textarea&gt;</code></a></p>

  <code-block language="html" label="Autocomplete values">{{ autocompleteExample | escape }}</code-block>
</section>

<section id="interactivity">
  <h2>Interactivity</h2>
  <p>Native attributes that control visibility, interaction, and editing — no JavaScript required.</p>

  <h3><code>hidden</code> and <code>inert</code></h3>
  <p><code>hidden</code> removes an element from rendering entirely. <code>inert</code> keeps it visible but makes it completely non-interactive — unfocusable, unclickable, invisible to assistive technology.</p>
  <p><code>hidden="until-found"</code> is a newer value that collapses content but lets the browser reveal it during find-in-page searches.</p>

  <code-block language="html" label="Hidden and inert">{{ hiddenInertExample | escape }}</code-block>

  <h3><code>popover</code></h3>
  <p>The Popover API lets you create popovers, menus, and tooltips with zero JavaScript. Elements with <code>popover</code> are hidden by default, rendered in the top layer when shown, support light-dismiss (click outside to close), and get a <code>::backdrop</code> pseudo-element.</p>

  <code-block language="html" label="Popover API">{{ popoverExample | escape }}</code-block>

  <div class="example">
    <layout-stack data-layout-gap="m">
      <div>
        <button popovertarget="demo-popover">Open Popover</button>
        <div id="demo-popover" popover>
          <layout-stack data-layout-gap="s">
            <p><strong>Popover content</strong></p>
            <p>Click outside or press <kbd>Escape</kbd> to close.</p>
          </layout-stack>
        </div>
      </div>
    </layout-stack>
  </div>

  <h3><code>contenteditable</code></h3>
  <p>Makes any element editable by the user. The <code>plaintext-only</code> value prevents rich text formatting and strips formatting on paste.</p>

  <code-block language="html" label="Content editable">{{ contenteditableExample | escape }}</code-block>
</section>

<section id="accessibility">
  <h2>Accessibility</h2>
  <p>Attributes that improve how content is perceived by assistive technology and internationalized correctly.</p>

  <h3><code>lang</code></h3>
  <p>Declares the language of content. Screen readers use this to switch pronunciation, and the browser uses it for hyphenation and spell-checking. Set <code>lang</code> on <code>&lt;html&gt;</code> for the page language, and on inline elements when the language changes.</p>

  <h3><code>dir</code></h3>
  <p>Sets the text direction. Use <code>dir="rtl"</code> for right-to-left languages (Arabic, Hebrew, etc.). The <code>&lt;bdi&gt;</code> element automatically isolates bidirectional text.</p>

  <h3><code>translate</code></h3>
  <p>Tells translation tools whether content should be translated. Use <code>translate="no"</code> on brand names, code snippets, and technical terms that should remain in the original language.</p>

  <h3><code>tabindex</code></h3>
  <p>Controls whether and in what order an element can receive keyboard focus.</p>
  <dl>
    <dt><code>tabindex="0"</code></dt>
    <dd>Makes a non-interactive element focusable in normal tab order. Use on custom interactive widgets.</dd>
    <dt><code>tabindex="-1"</code></dt>
    <dd>Focusable programmatically (via <code>.focus()</code>) but not via Tab key. Use for focus management targets.</dd>
  </dl>
  <p><strong>Avoid</strong> positive <code>tabindex</code> values — they override the natural DOM order and create confusing navigation.</p>

  <code-block language="html" label="Language, direction, and translation">{{ langDirExample | escape }}</code-block>

  <p>For ARIA attributes and patterns used by Vanilla Breeze web components, see the <a href="/docs/accessibility/#aria">ARIA Patterns</a> section of the accessibility guide.</p>
</section>

<section id="security">
  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>Attributes that protect your users from common web security issues.</p>

  <h3><code>rel="noopener noreferrer"</code></h3>
  <p>Prevents the linked page from accessing <code>window.opener</code> (which could redirect your page) and stops the referrer header from being sent. Use on all external links that open in a new tab.</p>

  <h3><code>integrity</code></h3>
  <p>Subresource Integrity (SRI) lets the browser verify that a file fetched from a CDN hasn't been tampered with. The browser checks the file's hash against the one you specify.</p>

  <h3><code>crossorigin</code></h3>
  <p>Controls CORS behavior for cross-origin resource requests. Use <code>crossorigin="anonymous"</code> when you don't need to send credentials, or <code>crossorigin="use-credentials"</code> when you do.</p>

  <h3><code>referrerpolicy</code></h3>
  <p>Controls how much referrer information is sent with requests. Use <code>referrerpolicy="no-referrer"</code> or <code>referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin"</code> (the current browser default) to prevent leaking URL paths to third parties.</p>

  <code-block language="html" label="Security attributes">{{ relExample | escape }}</code-block>
</section>

<section id="forms">
  <h2>Forms</h2>
  <p>Native validation and form association attributes that reduce JavaScript and improve UX.</p>

  <h3><code>pattern</code></h3>
  <p>A regex that the input's value must match to be valid. Pair with a <code>title</code> attribute to explain the expected format — this text appears in the browser's native validation tooltip.</p>

  <h3><code>min</code>, <code>max</code>, <code>step</code></h3>
  <p>Constrain numeric and date inputs. <code>step</code> controls the increment — the browser will reject values that don't align with the step.</p>

  <h3><code>minlength</code> and <code>maxlength</code></h3>
  <p>Set character limits on text inputs and textareas. The browser enforces <code>maxlength</code> by stopping input. <code>minlength</code> triggers validation on submit. Pair with the <a href="/docs/attributes/data-count/"><code>data-count</code></a> attribute for a visible character counter.</p>

  <code-block language="html" label="Validation attributes">{{ patternExample | escape }}</code-block>

  <h3><code>form</code> and <code>formaction</code></h3>
  <p>The <code>form</code> attribute associates an input or button with a <code>&lt;form&gt;</code> anywhere on the page — it doesn't need to be a descendant. <code>formaction</code> lets a submit button override the form's <code>action</code> URL.</p>

  <code-block language="html" label="Form association">{{ formAttrExample | escape }}</code-block>

  <p>For more on form patterns and the <code>&lt;form-field&gt;</code> component, see the <a href="/docs/accessibility/#forms">Accessible Forms</a> guide and the <a href="/docs/elements/custom-elements/form-field/"><code>&lt;form-field&gt;</code></a> element docs.</p>
</section>
